THE GAME
--------

  'Beadit' is a Workbench game where you link tiles of the same
type, horizontally and/or vertically, like a series of beads on a
thread. An important thing to remember is that there is a maximum
of 2 links for each tile...

  Link together, as best as you can, tiles of the same type, by
remembering the order in which the game creates links. This means
that according to the possible links that can be made between
neighbouring tiles: the first link will be upward, then to the
right, then downward and finally to the left. The greater the
number of tiles that are linked together, the better it is...
especially when a game board is completed...

  Avoid, as much as possible, isolating tiles. Because as the
number of isolated tiles is accumulated, if that number exceeds
10, the game will be over...

  Have fun!

